<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The German reparations crisis affected the U.S. economy by:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Improving international trade</option>
            <option letter="b">Triggering international banking crises</option>
            <option letter="c">Increasing American exports</option>
            <option letter="d">Strengthening the dollar</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Germany's inability to pay World War I reparations in the early 1930s triggered international banking crises. When Germany defaulted on payments, it caused bank failures in Austria and Germany that spread to other European banks. This banking crisis affected American banks that had made loans to European nations, contributing to the international financial crisis and deepening the Great Depression.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
